---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/content.css';
---
<BaseLayout title="Revit BIM Integration for Medical Equipment Planning | Estrelis.ai" description="Two-way Revit synchronization for healthcare equipment planning. Sync room hierarchies, equipment placement, and level data between BIM models and Estrelis. Supports Revit 2024-2026.">

  <section class="content-hero">
    <h1>Revit BIM Integration</h1>
    <p>Two-way synchronization between Autodesk Revit and Estrelis — keeping architectural models and equipment plans coordinated throughout the project lifecycle.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>The Estrelis Revit plugin installs directly into Revit and provides real-time synchronization between your BIM model and equipment planning data. Room hierarchies, level structures, and department assignments flow from Revit into Estrelis — and equipment data syncs back.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Room and level hierarchies imported from Revit models</li>
      <li>Equipment lists synchronized per room</li>
      <li>Building and department structure maintained across platforms</li>
      <li>Supports Revit 2024, 2025, and 2026</li>
      <li>Desktop plugin — no cloud middleware required</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Why BIM Integration Matters</h2>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Single Source of Truth</h3>
        <p>Room data lives in one place. When architects add or modify rooms in Revit, those changes flow to equipment planning automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Eliminate Manual Sync</h3>
        <p>No more exporting room lists from Revit and importing them into spreadsheets. The plugin handles synchronization with a single click.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Cross-Team Coordination</h3>
        <p>Architects and equipment planners work from the same room data. Changes are visible to both teams without email or file sharing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Equipment Placement Validation</h3>
        <p>Verify that planned equipment fits within room dimensions and meets clearance requirements before procurement.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Use Revit for healthcare projects?</h2>
    <p>See how Estrelis integrates with your BIM workflow.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary btn-lg">Request a Demo</a>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
